reviews: Lovely hotel, small and very quiet, located in a quality neighbourhood, close to Metro, restaurants and useful shops. For 5 of us (2 adults, 3 kids), we had rooms 305/306 - quite small, but courtyard facing and great for our needs - super quiet, decent showers and clean. Reception staff were really friendly and helpful. Breakfast was fine. Overall, you could do a lot worse than this hotel for a short trip to Paris. We'd come back again.

We had a lovely experience at Hotel Eden; very clean rooms and a bit larger than your average central Paris hotel; very helpful staff and good breakfast.
We had an issue with an overpayment and Olga sorted us out immediately.
Really great experience, would recommend and we’ll definitely stay again here when in Paris.

My partner, friends and I stayed at Hotel Eden 18-22 March. The hotel itself is fantastic- super clean, great location, and amazing customer service! From arrival till the moment I exited the door on the last day, my time there was absolutely perfect! This wouldn’t have been possible without the excellent service of Olga and another young lady, part of the reception/concierge team, that was there throughout our stay. We called in quite last minute to sort a birthday surprise for one of our friends but Olga still managed to arrange this for us and to an even higher standard than we were expecting! She helped us keep the secret when we came in and together we managed to surprise our friend and kick off an exciting holiday right within the first hour of our arrival! The team was also super helpful in answering any questions we had related to travel and even helped us out with some French on occasion - a super friendly team, amazing hotel. I would 100% stay again!! Thank you again Olga!

Excellent experience. Could not recommend this stay higher. The location was perfect as close to shops, transport, restaurants, medical and patisserie next door. The boutique hotel was extremely clean, quiet and comfortable bed. Staff were very helpful and also spoke English if needed. The breakfast wasn’t a feast but they provided variety and enough to keep customers happy. Loved our time here. Five stars from me.

Literally the worst service I’ve ever had at any hotel with the rudest front desk I’ve ever met. Ruined 2 days of my Paris trip. I’ve already told all my friends not to come here. Do yourself a favor, and stay somewhere else until they refrain their staff in basic customer service.

The staff was welcoming and friendly. After two flights and bad motion sickness, I arrived to check-in a few hours early (this was not promised) but they accommodated me and got me a room. It was warm, cozy, clean, and the shower was beautiful. The location of this hotel was perfect for me for the weekend, it was not far from a subway stop, and about 15 minutes by car to the bus stop I needed.

we had a triple room for 3 nights
the room was a little bit small
but we were shocked that the toilet was in a separate room other than the bathroom
however the location is good and the service was good
the staff were friendly
there was a bakery just next to hotel
the supermarket is only 3 minutes walking distance also the metro station

My fiancé and I spend a fantastic morning at Hotel Eden with a wonderful massage and spa session. We were able to utilise the Steam & Sauna rooms for an hour followed by a delightful tea with pastries. It was such a lovely experience, the staff were so friendly and we felt so welcomed and relaxed! Would come back and recommend to friends!

I and my colleague stayed in this hotel for 3 nights. It was clean and had very friendly staff.
We were happy because at reception Ms. Asal was very helpful and we asked her lots of questions about the city tour.
For sure we will chose this hotel again for my next trip to Paris.

I stayed in this hotel for two nights. It was a perfect clean hotel with friendly staff . Special thanks to Asal who was exceptionally professional, friendly lady , made me feel welcomed during my stay in this hotel.

We stayed here in a family room for a long weekend. Location is good - just a 2 minute walk to the closest tube and bus stop. Has a view of the Eiffel Tower just round the corner and a small shop next door for drinks, snacks etc. Staff were wonderful, very friendly and helpful. Gave us directions when asked, booked a taxi and great with the kids. According to my son the shower in the room was better than ours at home! Hairdryer and mini fridge in the room. Had a lovely stay.

The great service from the staff is the highlight, especially Tanguy. We were very satisfied, they always helped us with any concerns, very friendly and always attentive. The location of the hotel is perfect, with close access to public transportation and the rooms are just as described. Very clean and with everything in order. The space and amenities needed to have a good stay.

The staff was very friendly and attentive to us. We really enjoyed our breakfast at the hotel and the bed was very comfy. I highly recommend this hotel even during this pandemic situation they made us feel safe and very soon I want to come back. Thank You so much Hotel Eden

Nice and amazing hotel and the staff were very helpful and professional. The bed was very comfortable. The hotel is clean. Amazing location near the Vaugirard metro station (Line 12). You can find nice cafe, shops, supermarket nearby.

We had a great stay, the room we were in was very confortable.

We booked a spa and massage session, which was very relaxing, the masseur is kind and made us very confortable.

The staff is very friendly including the general manager, the hotel is very well located,restaurants, supermarkets and shopping center near by if needed. The Eiffel Tower is not far neither you can see it walking down the street.

We recommand !

An amazing hotel to visit ! I had such a good time, the customer service is amazing, always smiling. I was in a kind of dark mood with the current Covid19 situation, even though I had my first holidays since the beginning of the year. I had no expectations but this hotel lifted up my spirits ! Very spacious room, awesome breakfast, and the staff : everything there helped me so much to switch to the positive side of life. Even the manager came to ask me if I needed anything. Impressive work ethic and care for the customers ! Thank you again !

Very good location for this charming hotel
Silence and comfort , and the staff is very friendly and professional
Very good place for short or long stay . I found several car places for my car.
I did not take any breakfirst but I assume that it is fine

As a business traveller, I focus mainly on Tranquility, Price and Location. And these are the main reasons why I choose Hotel Eden while I am on a business trip in Paris.
Located on a quiet side of the 15th district of Paris, near the subway station Vaugirard, Hotel Eden is at a 15 minute distance of all the biggest Parisian Hotspots : Exhibition center, Eiffel Tower, Montparnasse Tower, Saint Germain des Prés district, the main railway stations,...
Regarding dining options, the hotel doesn't offer any but is surrounded by all kind of restaurants, from the finest like the one opposite the hotel to the famous Parisian brasserie on the square nearby.
Last but not least, I always feel welcome thanks to the very professional and friendly staff.
I often use the salon downstairs as a functional workspace, sometimes even as a venue to meet my suppliers and the staff was always attentive to all the details to make those meetings as professional as possible.
Hotel Eden is a safe choice while looking for accommodation in Paris.

An elegant parisian address, a beautiful space near to everything .
I found myself where the elegance and harmony of the hotel in the flawless service provided by a devoted staff. The breakfast had a lot of choices
made deliciously unforgettable,
The staff was very welcoming ,I felt like a very special guest like a member of the family, they were always available to serve me with verry good manners ,
The room was very clean and big .
I really thank all the team for their kindness.

I’ll definitely consider staying again in the hotel Eden the next time when I will come back to Paris. Conveniently located, stylish decorated,good A/C,we enjoy the breakfast,amazing staff 🔝💯and courteous.
Thank you for being such wonderful and gracious host.

What can I say about Hotel Eden 🤔???Excellent establishment with a Warm and Very Professional welcome. Room, Breakfast, Hamam and Very Neat Service. A special mentions for the ladies at the Reception.
⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

We reserved a hotel nearby that was atrocious and called this hotel at midnight. We were absolutely delighted with this last minute stay. Clean room, fantastic service, great breakfast. I would highly recommend.

Nice and essential hotel. The rooms are clean and well furnished.
It is located 20 minutes walk from the Eiffel Tower in a nice area with a lot of restaurants and shops.
The breakfast is ok, nothing special, mainly packaged food and not a lot choice. The hot drinks are out of a machine so a bit disappointing.

I have stayed in Eden for 3 nights, it was very good experience.the room was small but very clean and comfortable, breakfast was good and all staffs were very kind and helpful, special thanks to Asal who made me a free early check-in.

I loved this hotel, very clean and nice rooms, location is great, it’s close to metro and 15 minutes walking distance to Eiffel Tower, service is great, The cute receptionist name Olga was very kind to help us with directions which makes us easier to save lots of time in our short vacation. Management is very kind, I would definitely recommended this hotel 👍

Lovely hotel, close to the metro. Room was lovely with on suite shower room. The local area has beautiful parks and restaurants bars all to be enjoyed. Staff very friendly - the only bad thing was internet was very intermittent for our stay but staff tried to re-boot the modem a few times. Over all highly recommended.

I really enjoyed my stay at hotel eden. The front desk receptionist was friendly and helpful. Remember to ask to use the sauna or steam room at least a half hour before so they can turn on the heat! I will definitely stay here again. Fun area also!

Second to none hotel in 15eme. Metro stations, restaurants, shopping, and other necessities all within walking distance. Clean room, courteous and smiling staff, very cosy breakfast area and a very present and professional manager. Highly recommend. Good value for money.

We (2 adults and one child) had a pleasant stay there for 4 nights. It was comfortable enough for us, also the bathroom was adequate and not too small as others have stated here. In comparison to other feedbacks: we had one of the superior rooms which seems to be the only ones to suit 3 persons. The staff was very friendly in each situation, also during one morning were they forgot to announce before that due to a business event they had a shorter breakfast opening time. We had the choice to choose from the business breakfast which was the same as usual or to be served in our room. We had chosen the business breakfast and were interested of what was going on on the business event :-). The fitness room an sauna was quit nice. Breakfast really not bad with eggs, cold cuts and cheese; cereals and fresh fruits; different choices of coffee, milk and fruit juice.
The hotel is located in a non touristic area of Paris but only 20 minutes to tour eifel by walk and 5 minutes to one of the metro stations (we used for our daily sight seeing only metro: fast and you can have a stop on all interesting locations). Also the restaurants nearby the hotel were perfect (see my reviews therefore; we tried four different and all were very good).
Thanks to the hotel staff.

There were very few options in breakfast and everything was of very bad quality. The cereals and corn flakes were of the worst possible quality. The coffee from vending machine was pathetic as well. I could only eat bread butter during my four days stay. The rooms were very small and lacked basic 3 star hotel amenities like electric kettle, coffee etc. The towels in bathrooms were ages old, and of very poor quality. I had paid 160 euros a day for this hotel. I had expected much better experience at this price.

rooms are small, cramped. Modern, but not helpful. I arrived late, instead of checking me in and letting me go to my room the person at check in suggested I "take a seat"? Completely oblivious to what most travelers arriving around 10:30pm would most likely want to do... go their room.

Wifi did not work; There were neighboring guests entering and leaving their room approximately 20 times in a 20 minute span. even though there were only approx. 5-7 rooms on the same floor. each time a room door closes, the other room doors rattle.

When I called downstairs about the noise and the lack of wifi they did not pick up the phone. When I went down to speak to the "concierge" I found out why he didn't answer the phone... there was a "back in 10 minutes" sign at the front desk... completely unattended lobby at around midnight.

Breakfast buffet was average.

Our stay in the Hotel Eden was really nice. Our friends recommend this hotel after their experience. Room was clean. All staff very kind. Breakfast was really good. We can recommend this hotel. Viktor and Nora

Really nice hotel. Stayed there with my habibi for a week and we both loved it! Friendly personnel, really clean, nice rooms, got everything you need. Not far from the Eiffel Tower! Definitely would recommend :)

We stayed overnight. The room was adequate, clean and pretty nice for a budget hotel. The staff were great. The hotel was nice and clean. The breakfast was solid, tasty and convenient. If you're looking to stay in this neighborhood, this is a very good choice.

Visiting Paris on a short business trip, the hotel provided a very good accommodation.
We have made an upgrade from standard to superior room and had a nice surprise with an upgrade to a junior suite.
Hotel staff are all excellent and very special thanks to Raluca for her kindness and professionalism.
Definitely a good address to recommend.

Hello
My last business trip was in Paris so I choose The Eden as a Hotel, honestly I really apreciated that place because it's a quiet and well decorated, the furnitures was new and comfortables. Service was perfect and the team worker " MAGNIFIQUE "

I wish to comeback again :)

Asia

Lovely quiet boutique hotel. Great breakfast with plenty of choice. The small outside area is quaint and quirky in a good way.

A nice quiet location close to the metro 15. Staff are extremely friendly and helpful and all speak both French and English.

Very Very Nice, always smiling and available. acceptable approximation (public transport and businesses). A small note: beautiful renovation of stairs, super decoration with good lighting, but still a good cleaning after the work !.
I will come back without hesitation.

The hotel has a lot of charm, the room is very comfortable, the location is ideal and the staff is very friendly and welcoming.
Lovely hotel, nice rooms, excellent wifi, good breakfast, great location!

I really enjoyed the neighborhood,
The team was very kind and professional,
My room was cleaned all the time with a
Modern style, very good wifi .
Everything is very organized
I enjoyed the breakfast with the continental buffet ,
I liked the ambiance,
Many thanks to all the team

Marie-Sophie

Super convenient and classic decor. Big elevator, big queen bed, big bathroom with double shower heads with rain above and power hand-held nozzle. Helpful, professional staff. Ask for a back room overlooking the garden.

The hotel is located in a lovely area of Paris, there are multiple restaurants for breakfast and dinner within walking distance. The Metro is a less than 5 minute walk away. From our arrival at the hotel to our departure the staff couldn't have been more helpful, including housekeeping. They went above and beyond our expectations and changed our rooms at check in to ensure our two rooms were beside each other and that we had a double bed (despite it being our error booking two twins!). Lovely rooms, small but most Parisian hotels are the same, well decorated, spotlessly clean and quiet.

This review is based on the overall booking process and customer service.

I booked a double via the hotel website for a good price but the booking was swiftly cancelled by the hotel with no explanation. I requested an explanation and finally was told they do not accept a certain credit card even though they state the opposite on their official website. Well fair enough but you should simply offer alternative payment option and apologise for the incorrect information on the website. You shouldn't simply unilaterally cancel any booking without valid grounds. That is simply bad and indifferent customer service.

The hotel didn't offer any alternative payment option at this point so I needed to send another inquiry and request to use another alternative payment method. They told me to either send them my card details or make another booking. No-one in one's right mind is going to email their card details so I made another booking. Here comes the best part, at this point they were requesting almost a double rate per night and refused to honor the previous booking rate which they unilaterally cancelled without valid gounds. They twice offered me a lower rate which was still considerably higher than the original one so I ended up cancelling my booking.

I recommend you to avoid this hotel due to indifferent customer service and spineless reservation policy. There are plenty of similar or better options in the area and closer to city center where you'll find better service and won't risk your booking to be unilaterally cancelled by the hotel without valid grounds.

Hotel is located about 2 blocks from the bus stop and 4 blocks from the train station. Rooms are clean, but very small, especially the room with the toilet in it. The small room with the toilet was located about 20 feet from the actual bathroom with the sink and shower. They do make it known that they charge an additional tax of 2.53 euros per person per night and 15 euros per person per day for a breakfast that is definitely not worth 15 euros.

What they don't advertise is that they scam guests when calling taxis or drinking coffee. There's a coffee machine but as soon as you press the button they ask for your room number to charge you for it unlike in the US, where coffee & breakfast is usually free.

Do not have the hotel call you a taxi. This is the biggest scam they have. A taxi from the right side of Paris (where the hotel is located) to Charles DeGaulle Airport is supposed to be 55 euros for up to 4 people and 4 euros extra for each additional person according to the established rate posted in all taxis and on-line. The hotel scam artist receptionist will say that they cannot find any taxis at the 55 euro rate even if you supply her with a business card from an honest taxi company. Then they will pretend to call another taxi company and start speaking in French, but since that taxi company is only 75 euros, that taxi company will not have any taxis available. Finally the scam artist receptionist proceeds to call the 85 euro taxi company, and all of a sudden that taxi is at the hotel's enterance 10 minutes early. When I questioned the 85 euro taxi driver he shows me a text that the hotel has an established rate with them. The hotel likewise points the finger at the taxi company, but I am 1000% certain the hotel is getting a monetary kickback from the taxi company in order to scam their hotel guests. Any hotel doing business in Paris for as long as Eden knows the established flat rate to airports and Eden is definitely not looking out for it's guests, and instead illicitly profiting from guests' lack of knowledge of French language and Paris taxi policies.

The area was not too far a walk to the Eiffel tower (20mins), one subway ride to the Louvre (Tuileries side) and one bus ride to the Notre Dame cathedral so it's very central.
I have stayed in other parts of the city so I would say the area is safe for first time visitors. There are a variety of restaurants near the hotel to choose from and a Carrefour (supermarket) just up on the street. Breakfast is pretty basic for the price.

Excellent!

Eden Hotel is the place to be in Paris, tastefully furnished with comfortable rooms and quiet also prices are very interesting.
I enjoyed my breakfast every mornings.
The Staff is very NICE.

I'm glad that we picked Hotel Eden on Rue Blomet. It is located in a quiet area near small, quaint cafes. The hotel staff are very friendly. The rooms are clean and air conditioned!! Super Shuttle is available from Charles De Gaulle Airport at a reasonable cost. You can also use Uber and the public bus station.

We stayed one night at this hotel on our way to the south. It was well located and plenty of parking nearby. The room was clean and well furnished and the bed was very comfortable. The breakfast was nice too. The staff at this hotel were very friendly and kind. We had such a nice night that we stayed there again for one night on our way home. We had another comfortable night. I will definitely stay here again. Thank you

We just completed a week long stay in Paris at Hotel Eden. The hotel is small and in a not so touristy section of town...both of which I think are good things. Nice modern lobby and shared spaces with nice little workout room as well. The Vaugirard metro train station is 200 yards away and very accessible. Numerous restaurants and grocery/utility stores are all within 1-3 blocks in any direction. Eiffel Tower is closest main attraction maybe a 20-25 min walk at good pace but easy to access via metro train. The hotel is really quite nice. We stayed in a Superior Triple room (had 3 adult travelers) and had no issues related to space or cleanliness. Room was very modern, clean and sufficiently large for us. Great bath area with huge shower. Toilet room is separate and small but who cares. Bedroom is separate room with private door from toilet and bath and had great comfortable king bed with separate twin/pullout which was very good sized and comfortable. Decent amount of closet space and a small balcony to get some fresh air. We did not eat at the hotel so I won't rate the food. Breakfast was available for like 15eur PP which isn't too bad for a big city hotel but there are far cheaper options just steps out the door and we took those options. Room service was timely each day and did great job. Front desk staff were kind and spoke very good English (we are American) and made us feel comfortable. Our only issue was the air conditioning. We are American southerners who like to feel cool when we sleep. To be clear the hotel absolutely has A/C. You can set the thermostat to a maximum low setting of 20C which is about 70F. That would be fine except the A/C just can't match that output under heavy hot conditions. Weather was around 90F each day so we were careful to keep the room dark. Also on our own we purchased a throw away small fan ($20 at local store like Target .5mile from hotel) and plugged it in to supplement the AC. Once we did and being careful to keep the room dark and the bedroom door closed we were fine at night but surely not as cool as we normally would be. I suspect this is very normal AC functionality so if you expect arctic cold hotel rooms in Europe during hot weather you probably won't get it anywhere in this price range. But we bought the fan and left it there and was money well spent. That was really the only minor negative for the hotel. Overall great stay and very reasonable rate for a triple so would surely consider staying there again if we ever go back. If had been cool months would probably have given full 5 rating without hesitating!

Really nice hotel staffs: Olga, Mohamed, Manager, tall guy with moustache, and 2 breakfast ladies: Nacira and Alexandria.

English speaking, friendly and warm, can engage in small talk. Some even
taught me French language, ;D
Made me feel at ease, relaxed, and Special. :)

Housekeeping is attentive to your needs too, they clean up when i am
out, and did not disturb me at all. Changes towels and tidies up everyday.

Hotel is near Metro (Vaugirard) and Carrefour and Leaderprix (cheaper,
smaller), supermarkets are nearby. Downstairs next door a boulangerie sells bread and pastries and nearby
have a few too..bus stop is not far, 2 left turns from hotel and walk til u see Matsuyama, a jap restaurant,
bus stops visible from there.

Can see Effiel tower from hotel, walking there takes 25mins if u able to navigate well with google maps..otherwise, just take bus 80, or u end up getting lost for nearly 2 hours like me..:(

Expo is 2 metro stops away. Must enter from right direction, ticket cannot be re-used once u exit station.

Kettle and hot water (eau chaud) available at Lobby. May have calcium (white flakes) in kettle water, normal for france..(I didn know then..haha)

Toilet is separated from Bathroom, a
cubicle by itself. Big size ppl will have difficulty but ok for me.

Breakfast (additional charge) is a good spread, with crossiants, Pain au chocolat,baguettes, white bread, cheese, ham, jams and spreads..my favourites were the fruit puree, honey spread, and EGGs (cook by
yourself, experiment with the time and have fun exploring the doneness of each egg!). fresh fruits like
bananas, apples, kiwis, grapefruit.
Coffee dispensor and tea bags.

Just be careful not to go out after 10pm, can hear drunk people speaking loudly, especially more during weekends.

Overall, I will return to this hotel again if i have a chance to come back to Paris, because it is filled with warm people. 😊

Thank you for making me feel comfortable here. :)

Regards,
Ker Sin

Hotel Eden Is a lovely small and charming hotel. It is in a quiet, mostly residential section of Paris, offering a respite from the hustle and bustle of the more touristy areas. Rooms are very clean and staff is attentive. Although there is air conditioning, the upper floors are a bit warm since the A/C cannot be set below 20 C. A variety of options are offered for breakfast, providing a healthy and convenient way to start a day of site-seeing.

We booked 2 rooms in this hotel for 2 couple and 2 kids. We were given room 302 & 306. Rooms were nice and clean but too small for a family. In room 306, we had requested an extra bed but the bed was not made when we checked in. Staff was really nice and he prepared the sofa bed in no time. After putting extra bed, there was hardly any space to walk around the room. Same in room 302,no space at all. There was no tea/coffee facilities in the room so had to go down to get the hotel water in middle of the night which was not very convenient. Staffs we came across were very nice and polite. We wanted to book a hotel near Eiffel Tower but this hotel is bit far away.

Stayed at this hotel back in 2015 during our first time in Paris. Overall excellent value! Room was small but neat and clean. Modern decor. Got a package deal with our flight and very reasonable priced. There is a fabulous bakery (boulangerie) at the corner of where the hotel is located, and it has fantastic pastries. We bought delicious pastries there almost daily prior to the start of our day. We did not eat breakfast at the hotel. Very centrally located, we were able to reach all attractions visited via the Metro from here. Would recommend!

My parents and I stayed in one room (City of Love with your parents... why not?) and had the time of our lives. We expected to be totally cramped (in addition to cramping my style) but there was enough space in the room for all of us, which is truly an achievement in Europe. My wife's from Texas, where everything is yuuuuge, so this was a pleasant surprise. (Yep, I did Paris sans wife. I'll be hearing about this one for a while.)

The staff was very, very friendly and helpful. I wish I could recall the supervisor's name but imagine a French version of Stanley Tucci in The Devil Wears Prada. Sarah and Olga were the sweetest and went absolutely above and beyond on every request.

The hotel, including our room, is spotless. The shower is amazing - phenomenal water pressure.

Very cool neighborhood - many amenities nearby. Boulangeries... patisseries... even a Carrefour. Walk thirty paces to your left out of the door of the Hotel Eden and voilà! There's the Eiffel Tower.

Highly, highly recommend. We'll return soon... merci!

I don’t even know where to begin. I found Hotel Eden Paris the night I missed my connection to NYC and I couldn’t have chosen a better hotel to stay at. The hotel was so chic and so clean. The room was small, but that’s typical of Europe so I wasn’t disappointed. The staff was so friendly and helpful - lent us extra adaptors, etc. The location was perfect for Uber pickups and it was also close to the metro. Breakfast was delicious every morning. The staff was also so nice and professional . Coffee, water, juices, and sodas were always available. I could go on and on stay here! I WILL COME BACK FOR SURE

This is an decent hotel, with metro nearby. The rooms are very small but comftable but the size of the room is the standard for Paris. I have stayed here 2 times before and this was my last time.

I booked the hotel again because of the gym, however was the gym still as poor as the last time, although they said they freshened it up.

Breakfast is very very poor. If you like to pay €15 for breaffast you better get to the bakery next door and get a coffee and perfect sandwich for €6. Nor fruit or glutenfree?

Internet sucks big time, Really bad!!

Hotel is located in a beautifull part of Paris and if they just could fix the breakfast and gym, it would be perfect.

Hotel location was excellent, heart of Paris, metro and bus stations are walking distances and nice cafe around the corner.
Hotel is clean, friendly staff, nice breakfast, would consider it a good value for money.

A smaller and very cozy hotel located close to the metro Vaugirard Arr. 15 (metro 12). Very service minded and friendly staff, helpful and speak English. Good beds, clean and tidy, daily cleaning and ok breakfast. The hotel is situated in a quiet area, and even better you can see the Eiffel Tower from the nearest side road. Very Parisian. The rooms are not that big, but can be recommended if you are in Paris to see and experience the city.

This is my second review on TripAdvisor and I travel A LOT. What to say? The hotel is very clean the rooms are cosy comfortable well decorated and for exploring the South of Paris the location is perfect. This is one of those place you find sometimes in Paris, quiet street, relaxing place and for a price that makes it a very very good deal. Just try to find this type of location, this level of cleanness , this type of comfort in Paris for that price: good luck! People at reception are charming I was offered a coffee as I was working in the lobby listening to mellow music. People make place and this place is good and I will come back.

We had a great weekend staying at this hotel. It's very modern and clean, in a great location. The room was a good size and had a pretty balcony. Staff were all super friendly and welcoming. Would definitely recommend.

The Hotel was nice , clean and comfy, really helpful staff , we had a great breakfast over there !! Also really easy to get to Eiffel Tower from the location and you’ve got so many restaurants around , you’ll just need to pick one ! ☺️ Really pleased of the hotel , I would go again 👌🏻

Location is near a residential-feeling corner of Paris. It's not expensive, but was an excellent value, with buses & subways galore for travelling. However, while everything was great, the staff were really fantastic. Shout out to them for their 1) hospitality and friendliness, 2) knowledge for local eats (Le Cap was an amazing restaurant) and 3) their willingness to go above and beyond! I left my ipad air in my room and they mailed it to me in Rome. I would never want to go through the process again -- Italian shipping was a nightmare -- but the fact that Hotel Eden was willing to do it for me really made the hotel unforgettable in my mind.

We stayed in this hotel to celebrate our one year anniversary. This hotel did not disappoint at all! The staff were super friendly and room was very comfortable and clean! We loved the fact the hotel manager was always checking up on us to make sure we're comfortable!

Returned from a 2 night stay with my mother and cousin from Australia and this hotel was perfect. Fabulous views of the Eiffel tower at the corner of the street. Hotel clean, quiet fully equipped. Friendly staff. Set 1 mile walk from Eiffel Tower which was perfect to take in all the beautiful sites on the walk into the centre. Fantastic restaurants around the hotel. Perfect stay.

Just returned from 4 days in Paris. I booked this trip as a present for my boyfriends birthday I wanted something near the tourist sights and this hotel didn't disappoint!

Due to not having transfers from the airport we used the metro link (for €10 outside of Paris or €1.90 inside of Paris) this seemed like a cheaper option! The hotel is situated just a 5 min if that walk from the vaugaird metro link and 20-30 minute walk from the Eiffel Tower but if walking isn't your thing just use the metro as it's perfectly situated it takes no time to get around a perfect hotel for sight seeing!

Our breakfast was included in our booking with Secret Escapes even though the selection was disappointing we couldn't complain as we weren't paying but I wouldn't say it's worth €14 like they are charging if you haven't got it included

Our room was clean and comfy with a Juliet balcony it in a lovely old style building which I love

The reception staff all speak English with this being our first time in France in some places the language barrier was an issue but all the staff here helped us out and couldn't do more for you

Perfect little hotel in the best setting highly recommend

We went for a weekend with my boyfriend and the hotel was super nice, the staff from the reception were very helpful and gave us a lot of information about what to do in the city.

The breakfast is good, and the rooms are very comfortable!!!

Clean and modern room
Close to Starbucks and supermarket, easy access to the conference centre and Paris siteseeing - walked to the Eiffel Tower in 20 mins.

Staff very friendly and location felt very safe :)

The only disappointment was that Breakfast was poor value.

Hotel Eden was good just a few small things that would have made it great! Some lights in the bathroom were burnt out, and others would not stay on. The shower also would run for a few minutes then stop flowing as well as water temp continually changed. Our room door also had issues closing and it seemed like it was almost stuck on lock we advised the desk but nothing was done to correct the issue. Best part of this hotel is for sure the spa make sure you have that included in our price after a long day of waking!

Amazing customer service throughout the day. I had very friendly encounters with Tahier and Alexis. Great customer service shown from the jump. Room is comfortable shower is modern with glass. Easy to get to from the Metro. Guys I strongly recommend this hotel if you want great human customer service stay here- you won't regret it. 15 min power walk to effiel tower. Buy snacks closer to your hotel-the prices triple near the landmarks.

Have stayed here the last couple of trips to Paris. Short walk from the M12 which gets you into the city center in no time. Have had the hotel breakfast (sometimes included in the rate) as well as the local bakery and Starbucks a couple of blocks away. Room is clean, elevator sometimes slow as they only have one. Internet connection could also use an upgrade. But service a always friendly and efficient. If you want to stay away from the tourist areas, this would be the spot. Although you do get a nice view of the Eiffel around the corner.

We stayed here for 4 nights and I can't fault this hotel. The room was small but had everything we needed. The place was very clean with a comfy bed and nice soft pillows. In a great position near a Metro station and a 20 minute walk to the Eiffel Tower. Staff were very pleasant and helpful would definitely go back to this hotel. Highly recommend it.

Lovely hotel close to the Metro. The room was spotlessly clean, very comfortable with huge shower ensuite. The staff were very friendly and extreme helpful. The breakfast was excellent. Would definitely stay here again.

The hotel was very clean and well kept, the hotel staff were very nice and friendly.
The room was compact and maybe a little on the small side, but the beds we comfy - its a city break, which to me means, site seeing more than size of room. I would recommend this hotel and would return for another stay.
The metro service is just 5 mins walk at the top of the street and gives you direct access to the city within a 10 min ride for around 2euro.
Continental breakfast was nice and if you walk around the corner you have a spectacular view of the Eiffel tower - every hour from 9pm (on the hour) there is a sparkling light show for 5mins.

Hotel is nicely located, with easy access to Metro, Busses, restaurants and only a couple of kms from Eiffel Tower. however the rooms are way too small. we booked a superior room which only had a double bed (not even queen); no hair dryer, no iron board and no coffee maker. Bfast was available for 14 Euros per person, which was little pricy for the offerings. Bathroom and toilets are separate, toilet was smaller than the stalls in the plane. Rooms were clean and non-smoking.

I only wish I knew there was a Novotel very close to it, I would have gone for that... will not stay there again.

Staff was good and helpful.

Nice rooms, decent people, no disturbance, 3 mins to metro connectivity, 1 min to bus, lot of restaurants near by, they take up return taxi arrangements in early morning timings. Employees are helping in nature, giving inputs about places to visit etc are great.

Very cute, refurbished hotel. The rooms are tiny but is what you expect in that kind of buildings in Paris, very clean, with all essentials provided, perfect for a weekend or 4 days exploring Paris. Very close to the metro like 2 mins walk.

Nice hotel to stay in Paris. Rooms are small but nice. Good gym downstairs and simple but good breakfast. Service is excellent and reception super helpful. Would definitely come back! Thanks Eden Hotel!

My wife and I really enjoyed our stay at Hotel Eden. The rooms are modern, clean, and quiet. The rooms are small for sure. We enjoyed the breakfast of croissants, baguettes, meats, coffee, oatmeal, and juices. The staff was always very helpful. The wifi speed was acceptable, surfing the web was fine, but not for any downloads. The location is great for walking. We walked everywhere. It was about 30-40 minute walk to Louvre, Eiffel Tower, Notre Dame, etc. A block away from metro stop. We would certainly stay here again.

Just arrived back from a four day stay in Paris in hotel Eden. Absolutely loved this hotel. The staff were very friendly and helpful. We stayed in the superior room which was quite small but so luxurious. However, as we were out for most of the days the room size didn't matter. The hotel is located in a perfect spot. It is nice and quiet away from the crazy tourist spots however you're just 2km from the Eiffel Tower. There is a metro 2 mins up the road from the hotel which was great. I'd advise anyone travelling to Paris to purchase a Navigo pass before they go for the metro, it saves you having to have change constantly for your ticket. There is a Carrefore shop beside the metro which is so handy for drinks and food, rather than paying a fortune for a bottle of water near the tourist spots!! We didn't opt in for the breakfast in the hotel as it was €14pp. We got pastries and coffees in the bakeries nearby for less than €10. Unless you're looking to spend a fortune on food avoid the tourist spots for dinner. We paid €16 for two glasses on Fanta one day. There are a load of lovely restaurants if you get off the metro at Convention which are reasonably priced. Overall had an amazing stay in Paris, I would recommend hotel Eden to everyone and hope to go back soon.

My wife and I stayed here for two nights and *when* we return to Paris, this is the place we'll be staying again!
A two minute walk to the Metro, you can see the Eiffel Tower when you walk a few yards away from the entrance, lovely bars and restaurants nearby - you just can't go wrong.
It was quiet there, the staff were extremely friendly and helpful.
The room was quite small but that doesn't matter. We stayed in a superior room with a lovely walk-in shower, a separate toilet, a safe, mini bar and hair dryer.

We only had the breakfast one morning at a cost of €14 each which was a little steep but we had to leave early to get to CDG. We went to 'Frenchie To Go' the other morning which is also worth looking up.

Cost for a taxi from the Arc de Triomphe to the hotel, 10:30 at night was €12,50, a 10 minute ride.

All-in-all, you can't go wrong here, if you're looking for a room in a great location (about a 25 minute walk to the ET) in a quiet(ish) area, great transport links, this is THE place for you!

I remember this stay a charming. Professional helpfull staff, fine rooms and a proper breakfast! Nothing too fancy, not a gym or pool, but the rooms were just very good. The area is lovely and you'll be able go anywhere quite easily and swiftly. A very fine hotel!

We have just got back from a 3 night stay and are so glad we chose this hotel. It is modern in decor and spotless clean. The staff are very friendly and helpful in every way possible. Breakfast is continental but well presented and fresh, it was very nice. The metro is a 2 minute walk away and there are a few cafes and restaurants near by. A mini market, chocolatier and Boulanger are all close by as well. We would certainly stay here again and recommend it very highly.

Hi everyone,
I just spend a whole week at the Eden Hotel, the room is beautiful and the service was very good, the manager is a great person. Honestly this hotel is the best place to be.
Eden Hotel is my advise for you.

We were only due to stay one night at this hotel and as we arrived, we were informed there was a problem with their water and no hot water was available in a few of the rooms. We instructed to a nearby sister hotel (which was much inferior to the Eden) where we stayed in a very cramped and depressing room (apparently a superior room). I contacted the hotel on numerous attempts to request a small gesture of £20 be returned but I have been ignored ever since. Apparently the hotel and rooms are nice but the one rating is for the terrible customer service they provided to me in this instance.

This little hotel was modern and comfortable, a real it is a hidden gem. I went with my 9 year old son, and friends and we ABSOLUTELY enjoyed ourselves. The location is convenient to the subway, about 2 blocks walk, in a nice neighborhood. There were bakeries, sweet shops, fruit stand and restaurants on either side and across the street from the hotel. There is a breakfast served, which was a true Persian style continental breakfast. I have recommended this place to friends traveling to Paris. I would stay here again too.

We stayed at this hotel for 4 nights over New Years Eve and adored it! We were in the "Apple" themed room and everything about it screamed "charm". We learned the hard way that the lights only stay on when you leave your room key in the key holder. Our first night I stayed in and was attempting to read a map while my boyfriend went out to find desserts. He of course took the key and shortly after he had left the lights turned out on me. Oops! The toilet is in its own separate tiny room from the sink and shower. We are both very tall people so it was entertaining maneuvering around the room in general. Breakfast was simple yet delicious. The front desk was always helpful and friendly. The whole look of the hotel was adorable and we will forever look back and love our time staying there. Great location to the subway, shopping and food. PS the best crepes we had were up the street at a place called Le Vaugirard. There is a man in a little kitchen attached to the restaurant who makes them. We got nutella and banana crepes and they were AMAZING. Seriously, we got crepes every day we were there and out of all the places, his were BY FAR the best!

My friend and I stayed at this hotel for New Years Eve celebration 2016/2017. I want to start off by saying this is a very clean, refurbished, nicely decorated hotel, with a fairly spacious room, as European standards go. I was very pleased with the room and the quietness of the hotel. I was greeted on 12/30/16 by the man at the desk whose name I did not catch. He was so friendly and so engaging and so helpful. There were some problems with my friend getting there so it was kind of chaotic for me and this gentleman allayed all my fears. He helped me with my luggage and was just generally kind. The next morning, same thing. Raluca was the sweetest, most helpful and engaging girl, very wise about directions and Paris in general, which I appreciated.
The reason I give this hotel a 1 star is because of one employee in particular. Her name is Asal. Not only was she extremely rude and condescending, she was just down right rotten. Such attitude giving rise to the reputation Parisians have towards Americans, which I had not felt at all until I encountered this woman. I'm sure her defense will be the coffee situation. That is no excuse for her rudeness and abhorrent behavior.
I would highly recommend this hotel to all of my friends in the future and would stay there myself, except for knowing I would have to encounter this person. I would also mention this when referring this hotel to friends.
That being said, it is super close to the Metro entrance, there is THE best crepe stand right at that same corner and there is a supermarket also right there to stock up on waters.

We arrived at this hotel, on the first impression, found the staff very helpful and to our surprise this place was very clean with a warm perfume of freshness. Our stay was pleasant, when we return to Paris we will visit Eden again. It also has very good transport links to the centre of Paris. Recommend this hotel.

Rooms smaller in overall size, room and bathroom very clean. Very close to metro stop which was very convenient. You could be anywhere in the city within 30 mins on the Metro. Staff friendly and helpful.

a small hotel located at one of the better regions in Paris. the rooms are normally sized and clean, and the price is reasonable in Paris. Been there for 4 times for visiting local friends and not disappointed yet.

Booked the Hotel for the Christmas Weekend. Suites the budget. Friendly and very helpful staff. Located in the City Center and has well connected Metro to places like Eiffel Tower, Louvre Museum, Notre Dam. Nice menu for breakfast. Will definitely recommend for people around the world

I stayed for 2 nights with my sister for her 21st birthday.

I was pleasantly surprised. The room was nice and clean. The decor was really funky and the shower was amazing.

The staff on the desk were really lovely and helpful.

The hotel was a few minutes walk from the nearest metro station and very convenient.

What a gorgeous small hotel,next to metro Vaugiguard which could take us anywhere and we went everywhere including Marne La Velle,Arc De Tromphe etc!

The price was very cheap as we spent way below our budget ,so it's pocket friendly!15 arr is not a bad area with lots of restaurant,groceries stores and cafe!There is a Starbucks just three blocks awayI will recommend this hotel to my friends who want to visit and not break the bank!

I cannot rate our trip at the Hotel Eden highly enough. It was our first holiday away together and we had such a pleasant stay. The hotel staff were incredibly kind and welcoming, all spoke fluent English and greeted us every time we saw them. They answered all of our questions and allowed us to store our luggage in a locked room after checking out of the hotel in order to keep our bags safe whilst waiting for the Eurostar.

Our room was all that we expected from the hotel and more. It was exactly like the pictures; clean, modern, bright and quirky. We had a window onlooking the street with a little balcony, plenty of wardrobe space, a minibar and a (huge!) comfortable double bed. The shower was simply fantastic - obviously recently installed. Our room was cleaned every day when we were out of the hotel without not once being disturbed by any cleaning staff. We kept all of our valuable belongings in the safe which we set up easily upon arrival. The room had great sound insulation and was very quiet with the windows shut which was surprising in a busy street of Paris. The lights in the bedroom were lovely! The whole room was perfect.

The hotel itself is very modern, clean and instantly pleasant when you enter. The lobby and small dining area is very comfortable, and we were allowed to relax on the chairs in the lobby and also downstairs in the gym/spa area until 6pm even after we had checked out at 12pm that day! We didn't get a chance to try the breakfast as we thought it was rather overpriced at 14 euros per person per day, however we were made clear of this upon arrival and bought our food from the supermarket a two minute walk away from the hotel.

The hotel is located to the south-west of 'central' Paris in Vaugirard, on the dark green (12) metro line which is a 1 minute walk from the hotel as well as a bus stop which takes you to Gare du Nord (35 minutes on the bus/25 minutes on the metro). We found the location perfect for all our needs, with a Carrefour supermarket on the main street (Rue Vaugirard) where we bought snacks and the majority of our breakfasts, lunches and dinners. The Eiffel Tower is a 20 minute walk away from the hotel, Le Louvre Museum around 30 minutes and Notre Dame around 40 minutes. Of course they are much quicker via the metro, however we chose to walk almost everywhere as viewing the local area was very pleasant and also saved us money. Although saying that, t+ tickets which count for one bus/metro ride are only 1euro 90cents, and can be bought in packets of 10 so public transport is very cheap!

I honestly could not think of one thing to complain about the hotel, our trip to Paris was fantastic and we felt very safe and even looked forward to coming back to our room after a long day.

I should also add that we got our room for a fantastic price - what a steal.

Thank you to all the staff at Hotel Eden, I hope everyone enjoys their stay as much as we did.

Perfect if you attend a fair at Paris Expo. It's a 5 minute walking distance from the subway station Vaugirard. Classy hotel - friendly staff. Full continental breakfast. Good coffee. Very quiet. Plenty of tasty restaurants around.

this hotel was very dirty and bad service.room was very small. we had always internet problem and cleaning was awful. we always had shortage of shampoo and cleaning tools which is mandatory for any hotel

The hotel is great.

First of all, the staff are very respectful and helpful. The receptionist helped me a lot by showing me the location of touristic places on the paris map and metro stations near them.

The room is cozy as most of the european hotels, but it is very clean and nice .

The location of the hotel is very good. It is actually very close to metro station.

The breakfast is also superb. It is not the best breakfast in the world, but everything is delicious .

I stayed at Hotel Eden for 8 days. I was very pleased. The staff were absolutely terrific! They all spoke English very well and were helpful with whatever was needed- directions, calling a cab, getting an electricity converter, etc... I checked in early in the morning and while I had to wait a short while for my room, the front desk clerk made me feel so welcome and comfortable. I sat in the lobby work space (spacious and comfortable), but they also have a darling little garden for guests to sit and enjoy the weather, talk, etc...

The room was small, like most European hotels, but very clean and cozy. It was also incredibly quiet which is important to me because I don't sleep well in hotels.

It is located in an incredible area. I felt very safe even when I was walking back to the hotel alone at night. It's a few blocks from the metro (and Starbucks). There is a great bakery next door and multiple other bakeries, restaurants and charming little shops within walking distance.

This place was definitely worth the money and I'll be staying there again when I go to Paris.

I have been very satisfied by the team very friendly and professional ,
they really made me feel home like a very special guest .
very nice and helpful at all the moments I needed .
the location were convenient to commute, the neighborhood very charming and peaceful very nice restaurants, bakeries, stores very unique.
the rooms were pretty big and luxurious what ever I desired at the mini bar ,the coffee machine and delicious teas and also the bathroom were offered .
the breakfast was royal so many choices offered!
I really do recommend the place to visit Paris

The Hotel Eden was the right location for us and the service was good. The rooms have been redone recently and were quite modern (albeit they do have the Paris size - small). One part of the refreshed room that could have been larger was the bathroom. The shower was nice, but there was no vanity at all. The hotel is within walking distance of a real gem of an area on Rue LeCourbe.
